&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Birmingham Women&#39;s and Children&#39;s NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Head of BirminghamSystemic Training- 8B- 30 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for the post of Head of Systemic Training (HOST) which is part of Birmingham Womens and Childrens NHS Hospital Foundation Trust. The Birmingham Systemic Training Programme is a well established 4 year training course from foundation level to its qualifying course which is validated by Birmingham University. There is also asystemic supervision course within the programme. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, energetic leader to sustain and expand the trainingand the facultywhilst honouring the breadth of experience and knowledge since its existence in 1977. The post holder will have overall responsibility for the provision, management, delivery, accreditation, quality and development of the Systemic training program whilstbased within the inpatient adolescent mental health services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information please contact John Burnham at john.burnham1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
